{
  "doc_id": "14787",
  "text": "In most discussions of the Unruh effect, the relation between acceleration and temperature is demonstrated by evaluating the excitation rate of a moving UDW detector to leading order in time-dependent perturbation theory [CITATION_1] . For a uniformly accelerated detector, the excitation rate follows a Planck distribution at the Unruh temperature. This feature of the excitation rate is usually taken as validation of the notion of acceleration temperature.",
